com.ausregistry.jtoolkit2.se

Class CheckResponse<I>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ausregistry.jtoolkit2.se.Response
      • com.ausregistry.jtoolkit2.se.DataResponse
        • com.ausregistry.jtoolkit2.se.CheckResponse<I>
  • Type Parameters:
    I - the type of object identifier used in this check response
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ContactCheckResponse, DomainCheckResponse, HostCheckResponse

    public abstract class CheckResponse<I>
extends DataResponse
    Representation of the EPP check response, as defined in RFC5730. Subclasses of this must specify the object to which the command is mapped. Instances of this class provide an interface to access availability information for each object identified in a CheckCommand. This relies on the instance first being initialised by a suitable EPP check response using the method fromXML. For flexibility, this implementation extracts the data from the response using XPath queries, the expressions for which are defined statically.
    See Also:
    CheckCommand, Serialized Form
